  "Thai Lee is CEO of  $11.1 billion (sales) IT provider SHI International, which has 20,000-plus customers including Boeing and AT&amp;T.",
  "Born in Bangkok, Lee grew up in South Korea and moved to the U.S. for high school.",
  "A Harvard MBA, she did stints at Procter & Gamble and American Express before SHI.",
  "Lee and her now ex-husband paid less than $1 million for a software reseller in 1989, the predecessor to SHI.",
  "In 2018, Lee joined the board of Sonde Health, an affiliate of bio-pharma company PureTech Health that develops voice-based diagnostic technology."
